anuscript to address the following points: (1) Clarify all vague language and ensure consistent terminology throughout. (2) Standardize the presentation of baseline comparisons, especially for random search, ensuring consistent budgets and averaging. (3) Provide a clearer justification for specific design choices, such as the activation function mutation rule. (4) Correct all minor formatting and citation inconsistencies. (5) Ensure all claims, such as \"simple to use\" or \"any off-policy deep RL algorithm,\" are adequately supported or appropriately qualified based on the presented evidence.",
